stimulus:
Cognitive Task

This is a test of observation and clear thinking. You will be presented with patterns, one pattern at a time.

You will see a series of patterns that have a missing bit and possible pieces that complete each pattern.
user_agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_13_3) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/88.0.4324.192 Safari/537.36

stimulus:
The top of this problem is a pattern with a bit cut out of it. Look at the pattern, think what the missing bit must be like to complete the pattern correctly.

The pattern can be completed both down and across. Find the right bit out of the eight bits shown below the picture. For each pattern, there is only one correct solution.

Which piece competes the pattern?
user_agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_13_3) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/88.0.4324.192 Safari/537.36

stimulus:
In this example, Number 1 completes the pattern correctly downwards, but is wrong the other way. Number 4 is correct along, but wrong downwards.

The answer is Number 8, because it completes pattern both downwards and along.
user_agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_13_3) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/88.0.4324.192 Safari/537.36
